  "prompt": "Do flu shots really work?",
  "response": "Flu shots are generally effective, but their effectiveness can vary from year to year:\n\n1. Effectiveness typically ranges from 40-60% in reducing flu illness\n\n2. Factors affecting effectiveness include:\n- How well the vaccine matches current flu strains\n- Individual's age and health\n- Strength of immune system\n\n3. Benefits include:\n- Reducing risk of flu infection\n- Decreasing severity of symptoms if you do get sick\n- Lowering risk of hospitalization\n- Protecting vulnerable populations\n\n4. Even when not perfectly matched, vaccines can still provide some protection\n\n5. Recommended annually, especially for high-risk groups like elderly, children, and those with chronic health conditions\n\nExperts generally agree that getting a flu shot is beneficial for most people, despite not being 100% guaranteed to prevent illness.",
